The dramatic increase during the past decade in prostate-specific antigen (PSA) 
testing and prostate biopsies has resulted in the detection of large numbers of 
small lesions, an increase in the incidence of prostate cancer, and an 
increasing incidence-to-mortality ratio. Currently, the risk of being diagnosed 
